                            General Responsibilities and Duties
                    








            General Responsibilities and Duties
          

The general duties of the UIC Alumni Board include, but are not limited to:
a. Serving as the official alumni volunteer leadership voice representing the collective UIC alumni body
b. Fostering synergy to enhance and advance relationships between UIC alumni, the UIC campus and the university at large
c. Advocating for UIC at the city, county, state and federal levels
d. Mentoring students and alumni
e. Promoting life-long learning and connections
f. Recruiting, nurturing and encouraging UIC alumni volunteerism
g. Building, promoting and strengthening alumni outreach and relationship building
h. Supporting alumni relations strategies consistent and complementary with the UIC Office of the Vice Chancellor for Advancement and university goals at large







                            Nomination Process
                    








            Nomination Process
          

All alumni (Alumni are defined as individuals who have completed coursework toward or who have been granted a postsecondary award, certificate, or diploma including an associate, baccalaureate, masters, doctoral, or first professional degree, as well as post-baccalaureate or first professional certificate) are eligible to become a member of the UIC Alumni Board. Applications are accepted on a yearly basis. The application period is open January 1–March 31 of each year. Applications received after that date will be placed in the pool for the following year. For more information, please email uicalumni@uic.edu.







                            Terms and Expectations
                    








            Terms and Expectations
          

Members of the UIC Alumni Board serve two-year terms. These terms can be renewed up to three consecutive terms, totaling six consecutive years of service. All members of the UIC Alumni Board are expected to:
a) Attend and participate in scheduled meetings
b) Represent the UIC Alumni Board by attending and participating in various UIC campus related activities
c) Make a gift or get a gift to UIC that is meaningful each year
d) Recommend potential alumni to get involved with UIC
e) Actively serve on an UIC Alumni Board committee
f) Vote on new board members and elect current board members to serve on the Leadership Committee














